text: Edamulackal is a village in Kollam district in the state of Kerala, India. Edamulackal is near the second fastest growing town of Kerala, Anchal. Edamulackal is developing fast in education and service sectors. The land allows many kinds of farming. Farms use water from the Ithikkara river. == Demographics == India census, Edamulackal had a population of 22142 with 10586 males and 11556 females. == References == Category:Villages in Kollam district
